## Cushion Flanked by Trapezoids Ring

A cushion flanked by trapezoid side stones is the most architecturally dramatic three-stone configuration available for a cushion center. Trapezoids are step-cut, wide, and flat — they sit low against the finger and create a bold geometric platform that frames the cushion center with clean, angular contrast. The Blue Nile [Three-Stone Trapezoid Sidestone 14K Rose Gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-trapezoid-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-item-203681?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is priced at [$5,900](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-trapezoid-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-item-203681?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — the most expensive setting in this guide — because the trapezoid side stones require precision step-cutting to maintain their parallel faces and specific taper angles.

The visual logic of the trapezoid-cushion pairing is contrast-based: the cushion's soft rounded outline reads against the trapezoid's hard right angles, creating a tension between organic and geometric that defines Art Deco jewelry aesthetics. This combination is often called the "East-West platform" look because the trapezoid wings extend the ring's visual width dramatically at the finger. The trapezoid configuration works best with a 1ct or larger cushion center — at 0.75ct or smaller, the center stone can look disproportionately small against the wide trapezoid flankers.

Budget consideration for cushion-trapezoid builds: a complete ring pairing a [GIA 1.5ct G-VS1 cushion at ~$3,800](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) with the Trapezoid Sidestone setting at [$5,900](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-trapezoid-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-item-203681?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) totals ~$9,700. For buyers who want the trapezoid aesthetic at lower entry cost, pairing a [IGI 1.5ct E-VVS2 lab cushion at ~$1,200](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) with the same setting brings the total to ~$7,100 with no visible optical compromise.

## Cushion Half Moon Three Stone Ring

The half-moon side stone is the most visually harmonious flanker for a cushion center because its curved, D-shaped outline mirrors the cushion's soft corner geometry. Half-moon side stones curve away from the center stone like bookends, creating a continuous curved visual flow from one side of the ring to the other rather than the angular interruption that baguettes or trapezoids introduce. The Blue Nile [Three-Stone Half-Moon Sidestone 14K White Gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-half-moon-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-item-203679?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is priced at [$5,320](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-half-moon-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-item-203679?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and pairs most naturally with cushion centers between 0.75ct and 2ct.

Half-moon flankers are brilliant-cut rather than step-cut, which means they sparkle rather than flash — when the center cushion sparks, the half-moon sides amplify that sparkle rather than contrasting it. This unified sparkle character makes the half-moon-cushion three-stone ring read as more maximalist and glittery than the trapezoid version, which has a more restrained, architectural quality. Buyers who want the ring to produce visible sparkle from across a room consistently choose half-moon over trapezoid or baguette configurations.

A complete half-moon build with a [GIA 1.5ct G-VS1 natural cushion at ~$3,800](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) plus the Half-Moon setting at [$5,320](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-half-moon-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-item-203679?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) totals ~$9,120 — delivering the most unified, continuously sparkling three-stone cushion ring in this guide. Half-moon settings are also easier to resize than trapezoid settings because the curved half-moon geometry is more forgiving of minor prong repositioning during resizing.

