## Three Stone Cushion Cut Lab Grown Diamond

Three stone cushion rings with lab-grown center stones represent the best value-to-size ratio in this category in {{year}}. An IGI-certified 1ct E-VVS2 lab cushion costs approximately $680 — versus $1,891 for a GIA-equivalent natural — which frees budget to move into a more architecturally complex setting or upgrade to a 1.5ct center stone without exceeding $4,000 total. Lab-grown cushion cuts are chemically identical to natural diamonds, receive the same IGI grading, and produce the same optical performance; the only meaningful difference is market resale value, which matters only if you plan to sell the ring rather than wear it.

