## Three Stone Cushion Cut Natural Diamond Builds

Natural GIA-certified cushion cuts carry higher retail prices and significantly higher resale values than lab equivalents, making them the right choice for buyers who view the ring as a long-term asset or heirloom. A [GIA 1ct G-VS1 cushion modified brilliant Ideal cut](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) starts at $1,891 at Blue Nile — approximately 2.8× the price of a lab equivalent at the same carat — and the optical performance difference is invisible to the unaided eye. The case for natural in a three-stone ring: certified origin, provenance, and resale value only exist for natural GIA stones; lab stones do not retain those attributes.

